output_data.summary: Follow-up for Recurrent Major Depressive Disorder (*F33.1*) presenting with persistent moderate symptoms and inadequate response to initial 50mg dose of *Sertraline*.
output_data.reasoning: The patient reported persistent vegetative symptoms, anhedonia, and passive death ideation (though denying active suicidal intent), 4 weeks post-initiation of an SSRI, warranting dose escalation and a thorough safety assessment.
